Two separate issues here:

**1. Use `DynamicResource`, not `StaticResource`**

`StaticResource` resolves once at XAML load time and never updates. Switch to `DynamicResource` so bindings re-evaluate when you swap the merged dictionary:

```xml
<!-- âś— won't update at runtime -->
<Label TextColor="{StaticResource PrimaryTextColor}" />

<!-- âś“ updates when the resource value changes -->
<Label TextColor="{DynamicResource PrimaryTextColor}" />
```

Then swap themes by replacing the dictionary at runtime:

```csharp
var mergedDicts = Application.Current.Resources.MergedDictionaries;
mergedDicts.Clear();
mergedDicts.Add(useDark ? new DarkTheme() : new LightTheme());
```

**2. Prevent Activity restart on config change**

Android destroys and recreates the Activity when dark mode toggles. In your `MainActivity.cs`, declare that you handle `UiMode` changes yourself:

```csharp
[Activity(
    ConfigurationChanges = ConfigChanges.UiMode | ConfigChanges.Orientation | ConfigChanges.ScreenSize)]
public class MainActivity : MauiAppCompatActivity
{
}
```

Then optionally detect the system change and apply your theme:

```csharp
public override void OnConfigurationChanged(Configuration newConfig)
{
    base.OnConfigurationChanged(newConfig);

    bool isSystemDark = (newConfig.UiMode & UiMode.NightMask) == UiMode.NightYes;
    // swap your ResourceDictionary here
}
```

**TL;DR** â€” `StaticResource` â†’ `DynamicResource` fixes runtime switching; adding `ConfigChanges.UiMode` to your Activity attribute stops the restart.
